    "r_range": 2.117750419472486e-13,
    "is_independent": true,
    "explanation": "The Nash frustration pattern is independent of eta in the tested range [0.001, 0.1]. This is because all unstable eigenmodes arise from negative Hessian eigenvalues, and eta only scales the instability weight linearly, which cancels after max-normalization. eta is therefore a free convergence parameter, not a physics parameter requiring calibration."
